{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἔπειμι</b>, <br /> (εἰμί <br /><Level1><b>__A</b></Level1> <b>sum</b>) <i>infinitive</i> ἐπεῖναι: <i>Epic dialect</i> <i>imperfect</i> ἔπεσαν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 2.344: \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<i>future</i> ἐπέσομαι, <i>Epic dialect</i> and Lyric poetry -έσσομαι,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4.756, 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 13.99 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<b>to be upon,</b> with <i>dative</i> loci, κάρη ὤμοισιν ἐπείη [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 2.259; σῆμα δ᾽ οὐκ ἐπῆν κύκλῳ 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 591 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; in Prose mostly with <i>preposition</i>, ἐπὶ τοῦ καταστρώματος ἐ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 8.118; ἐπὶ [τῷ ποταμῷ] πύλαι ἔπεισι [prev. author] 5.52, compare 7.176; ἐπὶ ταῖς οἰκίαις τύρσεις ἐπῆσαν 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 4.4.2: _absolutely_, κώπη δ᾽ ἐλέφαντος ἐπῆεν 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 21.7, compare 2.344, 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 5.127, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 547, etc. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__A.2</b></Level3> <b>to be upon, be set upon,</b> of names, οὐκ ἔπεστι ἐπωνυμίη Περσέϊ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.53; so ψεύδεσι σεμνὸν ἔπεστί τι 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 7.23; τοῖσι λόγοις σῶφρον ἔ. ἄνθος 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 1025 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>to be attached,</b> μελέτη δ᾽ ἔπεστι παντί [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Anacreontea” 58.3; οὔτε τις τάξις οὔτε ἀνάγκη ἔπεστιν αὐτοῦ τῷ βίῳ 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 561d \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; especially of rewards and penalties, ποινά, κέρδος ἐπέσται, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 543 (Lyric poetry), 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Aves” 597; ἔπεστι νέμεσις 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 1467; ἔσχαται τιμωρίαι ἐπὶ ταῖς ἐπαγγελίαις ἔπεισιν 4th c.BC: Isaeus Orator 3.47, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 943d: _absolutely_, Ταραντίνων οὐκ ἐπῆν ἀριθμός\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] no count <b>was taken,</b> no number <b>was attached,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.170, compare 191 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>to be at hand, be present,</b> τίς τέρψις ἐπέστα; [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 1216 (Lyric poetry); αἰσχύνη 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 6.2.33; πιεῖν δὲ θάνατος οἶνον, ἢν ὕδωρ ἐπῇ 5th c.BC: Cratinus Comicus 273 (assuming variant)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὰ ἐπόντα <b>accidents</b> or <b>characteristics,</b> opposed to τὸ ὑποκείμενον, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD: Plotinus Philosophus 2.4.10. \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__A.3</b></Level3> <b>to be in</b> one's <b>possession,</b> ἀνέρες οἷσιν ἔπεστι μέγα κράτος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “hymnus ad Cererem” 150. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__A.4</b></Level3> <b>to be imminent,</b> ἐπόντος τοῦ φόβου τούτου [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.9; εἰ μηδεὶς ἐπῆν ἀγὼν μηδὲ κίνδυνος [prev. passage] \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__A.5</b></Level3> ἔπι for ἔπεστι (see. ἐπί [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus 11). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__A.II</b></Level2> of Time, <b>to be hereafter, remain,</b> ἀλλ᾽ ἔτι πού τις ἐπέσσεται [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 4.756 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <b>to be at hand,</b> οὐδέ τι δειλὸν γῆρας ἐπῆν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 114 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἐπεσσόμενοι ἄνθρωποι generations <b>to come,</b> Oracle texts cited in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.77, epigram cited in 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 3.184 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐπεσσόμενοι alone, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 12.11. \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__A.III</b></Level2> <b>to be set over,</b> τισί [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.96, 8.71; ἔπεστί σφι δεσπότης νόμος [prev. author] 7.104; τίς δὲ ποιμάνωρ ἔ.; 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 241 (troch.), compare 555 (Lyric poetry). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__A.IV</b></Level2> <b>to be added, be over and above,</b> of numbers, χιλιάδες ἔπεισι ἐπὶ ταύτῃσι ἑπτά [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.184, compare 185 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐπόντων τεσσάρων <b>plus</b> four, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Arrianus Historicus “Tactica” 10.8 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; τὰ ἐπεσόμενα τούτοις (i.e. προβάτοις) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Arch.Papyrus” 1.64 (2nd c.BC). \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__A.V</b></Level2> <b>to be added</b> as confirmation, ἔξορκος ἐπέσσεται [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 13.99. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__A.V.2</b></Level3> <b>belong in addition,</b> τὰν περὶ αὐτὸ χώραν ἐπείμειν Πριανέων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Schwyzer” 289.27 (2nd c.BC). \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G7376","accentedUnicode":"ἔπειμι","shortDef":"be used","mediumDef":"be used","stepGloss":"be used","stepTransliteration":"epeimi","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}